<HEADLINE>
FT  16 MAR 92 / Construction Contracts: Water supplies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
EC HARRIS has been appointed by the Sydney Water Board, Australia, to review
tender documentation and estimates on four water-purification contracts with
a total value of AusDollars 600m (Pounds 257m).
They will be built and operated under a 'build own operate transfer' style
contract with a transfer option at the end of the term.
Three of the projects, Avon, MacArthur and Woronara, which are based inland
from Sydney, will each supply 200 megalitres of drinking water a day to the
city's suburbs.
The largest project, Prospect, will have a joint module capacity of 600
megalitres a day to meet Sydney's water demand in 1997. Further modules will
upgrade total plant capacity to 3000 megalitres a day to meet the expected
demand in the year 2000.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
<PAGE>
