<HEADLINE>
FT  16 MAR 92 / Italian Government invokes special powers
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GRAHAM
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ROME
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Italian government yesterday invoked special powers to cancel a proposed
strike by air traffic controllers called for today, Robert Graham reports
from Rome. Similar powers are likely to be invoked for another stoppage
planned by different air traffic control unions for tomorrow.
Mr Carlo Bernini, transport minister, ordered air traffic controllers to
report to work as normal; those defying the order could face up to five
years' jail. Strikes last Friday and Saturday by the air traffic controllers
forced cancellation of over 80 per cent of all flights in and out of Italy.
The stoppages were called as part of a dispute over work conditions.
