FT  16 MAR 92 / EC set to agree banking standards
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW HILLS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Ministers are expected to agree today on Community-wide standards to prevent
banks and credit institutions collapsing by lending too much to individual
clients, Andrew Hills reports from Brussels.
Portugal, which holds the EC presidency, is to put forward a compromise
eventually preventing lenders granting loans worth more than 25 per cent of
their shareholders' funds to a single borrower.
A single loan worth more than 10 per cent of shareholders' funds would have
to be cleared with national banking supervisors.
