FT  16 MAR 92 / Observer: Won't do nicely
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A colleague shopping for a new television in London's Tottenham Court Road,
home of cheap consumer electronics, was told the set of his choice would
cost him a mere Pounds 175 - until he brought out his American Express card.
'Haven't you got Visa?', said the shopkeeper. 'I can't go down to Pounds 175
on American Express.'
