Many of the chancellor's Budget proposals were enacted into legislation
this week and others by Treasury Orders. Unless repealed by a Labour or
coalition government, the following timetable shows when they will (or
have) come into effect:
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
TAX RATES AND ALLOWANCES
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
New 20 per cent tax band                    6 April 92
Personal allowance raised                   6 April 92*
Age allowances up                           6 April 92*
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
CAPITAL GAINS TAX
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Exemptions raised                           6 April 92
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
INHERITANCE TAX
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Threshold raised to Pounds 147,000          6 April 92+
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
PENSIONS
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Increase in income support rates            October 92
Pensions cap up                             6 April 92
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
PEPS
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Pounds 3,000 limit on investment and
  unit trusts lifted to Pounds 6,000        6 April 92
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
NATIONAL SAVINGS
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Guaranteed growth bond                         July 92
Limit on income bond holdings up              April 92
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
CARS
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Duty rise on petrol                        10 March 92
Vehicle Excise Duty up                     11 March 92
Tax on price of new cars cut               11 March 92
Rise in company car scale charges           6 April 92
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
DUTY RISES ON ALCOHOL &amp; TOBACCO            10 March 92
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
BETTING
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Duty down                                   1 April 92
* revised PAYE codes for most people
take effect on the first pay day after
17 May 92
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
The following measures depend on the Conservatives being re-elected:
Married Couple's allowance transfer 6 April 93
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
+Remaining Pounds 3,000 rise of IHT threshold
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
BES to end 31 December 93
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Minimum limit for Gift Aid 1 July 92
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
