<HEADLINE>
FT  14 MAR 92 / UK Company News: Rothschild expected to advise on sale of
MGN
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
NM ROTHSCHILD, the merchant bank, is expected to be appointed next week as
adviser on the sale of Mirror Group Newspapers in the first indications of
preparations for the disposal of the group.
It is believed that the majority shareholding in MGN could be ready for sale
by the summer, although no final timetable has been drawn up.
Partners at Arthur Andersen, the accountancy firm, who are acting as
administrators to the private business empire of the late Mr Robert Maxwell,
are expected to make a final decision on the appointment of advisers within
the next few days. They are believed to be favouring Rothschild over a rival
bid from Morgan Grenfell.
The purchaser of MGN might not be able to take control until towards the end
of the year as any sale may need ratification by the Monopolies and Mergers
Commission.
The administrators are believed to have received expressions of interest
from at least ten potential purchasers.
The sale of the principal UK businesses of AGB, the market research company
from the administrators of the private empire of Robert Maxwell, to Addison
Consultancy was completed yesterday.
A rights issue offer document issued last month to raise money to buy the
AGB businesses, showed that it was paying Pounds 14.75m.
Sales of other AGB companies overseas are expected within the next few
weeks.
