<TEXT>
CONSERVATIVE business managers at Westminster have withdrawn the party whip
from Mr John Browne, Tory MP for Winchester, after his decision to stand
against the officially selected candidate in the seat on April 9.
The penalty, the ultimate sanction of whips at the Commons, means Mr Browne
